#### [NEW] [whatsapp_ws.py](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/Et-AI_Hack/ET-AI-Hack/backend/app/websockets/whatsapp_ws.py)

WebSocket handler that:
1. Accepts frontend WebSocket connection
2. Connects to the Node.js bridge WebSocket (`ws://localhost:3001/ws`)
3. Forwards events (QR code, authentication, ready, new messages) from bridge → frontend
4. Forwards commands from frontend → bridge (if needed)

This acts as a relay so the frontend only talks to the FastAPI backend, keeping the architecture clean.

